{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_rTFJDjvLv3fHKsNnzgI9JWyz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the necessary information to conduct the plan review. Let me analyze the findings.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Review Report for TST-001\n\nBased on my analysis of the PRD, research findings, and context pack, here is my comprehensive plan review:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ticket\": \"TST-001\",\n  \"overall_status\": \"warn\",\n  \"verdict\": \"PENDING_CHANGES\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"critical\",\n      \"category\": \"sequencing\",\n      \"issue\": \"PRD section 8 mentions 'WebSocket push notifications infrastructure' in Phase 2, but Q5 decision is 'Polling' (30s interval). This is a direct contradiction between AIDD:ROLL_OUT (which correctly states Polling) and section 8 milestones.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Update PRD section 8 to replace 'WebSocket push notifications infrastructure' with 'Polling-based session sync endpoint' and 'Frontend WebSocket integration' with 'Frontend polling integration'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"major\",\n      \"category\": \"dependencies\",\n      \"issue\": \"Research indicates no Spring Security in classpath (spring-boot-starter-security missing from build.gradle), but PRD does not explicitly list adding this dependency as a required step.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Add explicit dependency requirement to PRD section 7 (Constraints): 'Must add spring-boot-starter-security to backend-mcp/build.gradle'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"major\",\n      \"category\": \"dependencies\",\n      \"issue\": \"Research shows SSE infrastructure already exists and is used for flows/MCP, but PRD AIDD:ROLL_OUT jumps directly to Polling without evaluating SSE as a potentially more efficient option.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Document the decision rationale in AIDD:DECISIONS: Why polling was chosen over existing SSE infrastructure (e.g., simpler implementation, unidirectional nature sufficient for role updates).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"major\",\n      \"category\": \"integration\",\n      \"issue\": \"No database migration plan for audit_log table is documented in PRD. Research clearly identifies this as a gap requiring Liquibase migration.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Add explicit task to Phase 1: 'Create Liquibase migration for audit_log table with schema: timestamp, user_id (profile_key), action, target_resource, result'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"minor\",\n      \"category\": \"risks\",\n      \"issue\": \"AIDD:RISKS mentions 'Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism' but the mitigation is outdated (mentions WebSocket).\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Update risk mitigation to: 'Polling with 30s interval; manual refresh fallback; session version tracking to detect stale state'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"minor\",\n      \"category\": \"integration\",\n      \"issue\": \"PRD section 6.3 AC-3 states 'Frontend role guards update within 30 seconds' but AIDD:ACCEPTANCE and AIDD:METRICS specify '≤ 5 seconds'.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Standardize on 5-second target and update AC-3 to: 'Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of session change (via 30s polling with optimistic updates)'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"info\",\n      \"category\": \"dependencies\",\n      \"issue\": \"Research AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS lists 4 unresolved technical questions (Spring Security vs custom filters, profile-to-role mapping, WebSocket vs SSE, role source of truth) that should be resolved before implementation.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Transfer these questions to PRD AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS and resolve: Q1=Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security), Q2=Roles from profile service via X-Profile-Key, Q3=Polling (not SSE/WebSocket), Q4=Profile service is source of truth.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Synchronize PRD section 8 with AIDD:ROLL_OUT - replace all WebSocket references with Polling\",\n    \"Add explicit dependency addition task: spring-boot-starter-security to build.gradle\",\n    \"Document database migration for audit_log table in Phase 1\",\n    \"Resolve and document the 4 open technical questions from research in PRD AIDD:DECISIONS\",\n    \"Clarify backend role validation approach: cache vs profile service call per request\",\n    \"Add rate limiting requirements for polling endpoint to section 6.2 NFRs\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe implied implementation plan from PRD sections 8, 9, and AIDD:ROLL_OUT has **critical inconsistencies** that must be resolved before implementation can begin:\n\n1. **Critical**: Section 8 still references WebSocket infrastructure while Q5 and AIDD:ROLL_OUT correctly specify Polling\n2. **Major**: Missing explicit dependency addition for Spring Security\n3. **Major**: Missing database migration plan for audit_log table\n4. **Minor**: Inconsistent timing requirements (5s vs 30s) between metrics and acceptance criteria\n\nThe 4-phase rollout structure in AIDD:ROLL_OUT is sound and well-sequenced with appropriate feature flags and rollback mechanisms. However, the plan cannot be approved until the WebSocket/Polling contradiction is resolved and the missing dependency/migration steps are documented.\n\n**Status**: PENDING_CHANGES - PRD requires synchronization between sections before implementation."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a945737ab60431461 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 21396\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 47246</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7744ce0-fdf6-47dd-ae34-edb35fc5dbd2","uuid":"29c66f82-4515-418c-9876-a43d232b5988","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are the feature-dev-aidd:plan-reviewer subagent for ticket TST-001.\n\n## Your Task\nSince there is no explicit plan file at `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.plan.md`, review the implementation plan implied by:\n1. The PRD at `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md` (sections 8, 9, AIDD:ROLL_OUT)\n2. The research findings at `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n\n## Review Focus\n1. **Implementation Phases**: Are the 4 phases in AIDD:ROLL_OUT realistic and well-sequenced?\n2. **Feature Flags**: Are rollback mechanisms adequate?\n3. **Risk Mitigation**: Are the identified risks properly addressed?\n4. **Technical Dependencies**: Are dependencies (Spring Security, WebSocket vs Polling) correctly identified?\n5. **Integration Points**: Are the backend/frontend integration points clear?\n\n## Plan Review Report Output\nProduce findings in this format:\n```json\n{\n  \"ticket\": \"TST-001\",\n  \"overall_status\": \"ready|warn|blocked\",\n  \"verdict\": \"APPROVED|PENDING_CHANGES|BLOCKED\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"critical|major|minor|info\",\n      \"category\": \"sequencing|dependencies|risks|integration\",\n      \"issue\": \"description of the issue\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"how to fix\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"specific recommendation for plan improvement\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Key Issues to Check\n1. PRD section 8 mentions \"WebSocket push notifications\" but Q5 decision is \"Polling\" - inconsistency\n2. Research suggests SSE exists, but PRD doesn't leverage it\n3. No Spring Security in classpath - need to add dependency\n4. Plan needs database migration for audit_log table\n\nOutput your review results to stdout.","agentId":"a945737ab60431461","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the necessary information to conduct the plan review. Let me analyze the findings.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Review Report for TST-001\n\nBased on my analysis of the PRD, research findings, and context pack, here is my comprehensive plan review:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ticket\": \"TST-001\",\n  \"overall_status\": \"warn\",\n  \"verdict\": \"PENDING_CHANGES\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"critical\",\n      \"category\": \"sequencing\",\n      \"issue\": \"PRD section 8 mentions 'WebSocket push notifications infrastructure' in Phase 2, but Q5 decision is 'Polling' (30s interval). This is a direct contradiction between AIDD:ROLL_OUT (which correctly states Polling) and section 8 milestones.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Update PRD section 8 to replace 'WebSocket push notifications infrastructure' with 'Polling-based session sync endpoint' and 'Frontend WebSocket integration' with 'Frontend polling integration'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"major\",\n      \"category\": \"dependencies\",\n      \"issue\": \"Research indicates no Spring Security in classpath (spring-boot-starter-security missing from build.gradle), but PRD does not explicitly list adding this dependency as a required step.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Add explicit dependency requirement to PRD section 7 (Constraints): 'Must add spring-boot-starter-security to backend-mcp/build.gradle'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"major\",\n      \"category\": \"dependencies\",\n      \"issue\": \"Research shows SSE infrastructure already exists and is used for flows/MCP, but PRD AIDD:ROLL_OUT jumps directly to Polling without evaluating SSE as a potentially more efficient option.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Document the decision rationale in AIDD:DECISIONS: Why polling was chosen over existing SSE infrastructure (e.g., simpler implementation, unidirectional nature sufficient for role updates).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"major\",\n      \"category\": \"integration\",\n      \"issue\": \"No database migration plan for audit_log table is documented in PRD. Research clearly identifies this as a gap requiring Liquibase migration.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Add explicit task to Phase 1: 'Create Liquibase migration for audit_log table with schema: timestamp, user_id (profile_key), action, target_resource, result'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"minor\",\n      \"category\": \"risks\",\n      \"issue\": \"AIDD:RISKS mentions 'Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism' but the mitigation is outdated (mentions WebSocket).\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Update risk mitigation to: 'Polling with 30s interval; manual refresh fallback; session version tracking to detect stale state'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"minor\",\n      \"category\": \"integration\",\n      \"issue\": \"PRD section 6.3 AC-3 states 'Frontend role guards update within 30 seconds' but AIDD:ACCEPTANCE and AIDD:METRICS specify '≤ 5 seconds'.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Standardize on 5-second target and update AC-3 to: 'Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of session change (via 30s polling with optimistic updates)'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"info\",\n      \"category\": \"dependencies\",\n      \"issue\": \"Research AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS lists 4 unresolved technical questions (Spring Security vs custom filters, profile-to-role mapping, WebSocket vs SSE, role source of truth) that should be resolved before implementation.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Transfer these questions to PRD AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS and resolve: Q1=Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security), Q2=Roles from profile service via X-Profile-Key, Q3=Polling (not SSE/WebSocket), Q4=Profile service is source of truth.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Synchronize PRD section 8 with AIDD:ROLL_OUT - replace all WebSocket references with Polling\",\n    \"Add explicit dependency addition task: spring-boot-starter-security to build.gradle\",\n    \"Document database migration for audit_log table in Phase 1\",\n    \"Resolve and document the 4 open technical questions from research in PRD AIDD:DECISIONS\",\n    \"Clarify backend role validation approach: cache vs profile service call per request\",\n    \"Add rate limiting requirements for polling endpoint to section 6.2 NFRs\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe implied implementation plan from PRD sections 8, 9, and AIDD:ROLL_OUT has **critical inconsistencies** that must be resolved before implementation can begin:\n\n1. **Critical**: Section 8 still references WebSocket infrastructure while Q5 and AIDD:ROLL_OUT correctly specify Polling\n2. **Major**: Missing explicit dependency addition for Spring Security\n3. **Major**: Missing database migration plan for audit_log table\n4. **Minor**: Inconsistent timing requirements (5s vs 30s) between metrics and acceptance criteria\n\nThe 4-phase rollout structure in AIDD:ROLL_OUT is sound and well-sequenced with appropriate feature flags and rollback mechanisms. However, the plan cannot be approved until the WebSocket/Polling contradiction is resolved and the missing dependency/migration steps are documented.\n\n**Status**: PENDING_CHANGES - PRD requires synchronization between sections before implementation."}],"totalDurationMs":47246,"totalTokens":21396,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":793,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":19456,"output_tokens":1147,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
