{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_YuHZ7znms2CsrcJDXLovLRee","type":"tool_result","content":"    80→## AIDD:RISKS\n    81→- Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\n    82→- Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\n    83→- Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\n    84→\n    85→## AIDD:DECISIONS\n    86→- Live RBAC enforcement required per FS-RBAC-03 spec → compliance requirement\n    87→- Frontend sync without refresh → UX requirement for seamless role updates\n    88→- **Q1**: Critical APIs = все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n    89→- **Q2**: Текущая реализация = X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n    90→- **Q3**: Frontend = React + Zustand (not Redux)\n    91→- **Q4**: Audit logs = база данных (отдельная таблица)\n    92→- **Q5**: Session sync = Polling (fallback approach, simpler to implement)\n    93→\n    94→## AIDD:GOALS\n    95→- Enforce live RBAC across critical APIs\n    96→- Add auditable role operations trail\n    97→- Synchronize frontend role guards with live session updates\n    98→\n    99→## AIDD:NON_GOALS\n   100→- UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n   101→- Migration of historical access logs\n   102→- Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n   103→\n   104→## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n   105→- AC-1: Critical APIs return 403 for unauthorized role access\n   106→- AC-2: All role operations are logged with timestamp, user, action\n   107→- AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of session change\n   108→\n   109→## AIDD:METRICS\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7744ce0-fdf6-47dd-ae34-edb35fc5dbd2","uuid":"15dde545-291f-496c-80e9-0ed444262dce","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md","content":"## AIDD:RISKS\n- Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\n- Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\n- Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\n\n## AIDD:DECISIONS\n- Live RBAC enforcement required per FS-RBAC-03 spec → compliance requirement\n- Frontend sync without refresh → UX requirement for seamless role updates\n- **Q1**: Critical APIs = все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n- **Q2**: Текущая реализация = X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n- **Q3**: Frontend = React + Zustand (not Redux)\n- **Q4**: Audit logs = база данных (отдельная таблица)\n- **Q5**: Session sync = Polling (fallback approach, simpler to implement)\n\n## AIDD:GOALS\n- Enforce live RBAC across critical APIs\n- Add auditable role operations trail\n- Synchronize frontend role guards with live session updates\n\n## AIDD:NON_GOALS\n- UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n- Migration of historical access logs\n- Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n\n## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n- AC-1: Critical APIs return 403 for unauthorized role access\n- AC-2: All role operations are logged with timestamp, user, action\n- AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of session change\n\n## AIDD:METRICS","numLines":30,"startLine":80,"totalLines":279}}}
